SIMPLE: imperceptible
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imperceptible
<hw>Im`per*cep"ti*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>perceptible</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>imperceptible</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not perceptible; not to be
apprehended or cognized by the senses; not discernible by the mind; not
easily apprehended.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Almost <qex>imperceptible</qex> to the touch.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Its operation is slow, and in some cases almost
<qex>imperceptible</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Im`per*cep"ti*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Im`per*cep"ti*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their . . . subtilty and <qex>imperceptibleness</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir M. Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imperception</ent>⟦br⟧
